Officials say the newborn was found at the Ubuntu House two weeks ago. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town police have appealed for help in tracing the whereabouts of a mother who abandoned her infant at a Goodwood child care centre.Officials say the newborn was found at the Ubuntu House two weeks ago.The police's Noloyiso Rwexana says: Anyone who knows the whereabouts of the woman or family members of the child is requested to contact investigating officer Constable Dada at 021 592 7097. 